Identify all of the following equations that have a solution of -2?
\begin{align*}
\text{I)}\ & 3(x+7)=5(x+5) &
\text{II)}\ & x^2+x-6=0\\
\text{III)}\ & 2(x-4)=x-10  &
\text{IV)}\ & x^2=4 \\
\end{align*} 

\begin{align*}
\text{A)}\ & I and III &
\text{B)}\ & II and IV\\
\text{C)}\ & I, II and IV  &
\text{D)}\ & I, III and IV\\
\end{align*}
